parse: Verb - Present Indicative Middle or Passive - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To call to myself, summon. Middle voice from pros and kaleo; to call toward oneself, i.e. Summon, invite.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Twelve; the usual way in which the Twelve apostles of Jesus are referred to. From duo and deka; two and ten, i.e. A dozen.

str2: To begin. Middle voice of archo; to commence.
From apo and stello; set apart, i.e. to send out literally or figuratively.

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To offer, give; I put, place. A prolonged form of a primary verb; to give.

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
From exesti; privilege, i.e. force, capacity, competency, freedom, or mastery, delegated influence.
